<paragraph blockId="10.[151,630,1845,1907]" box="[151,235,1881,1907]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">
(
<figureCitation box="[160,226,1881,1907]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1900,1925]" captionTargetBox="[163,1414,184,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1430,174,1880]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Balala hainana Tang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. ♂, A–I Holotype: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and thorax, lateral view; D. Habitus, ventral view; E. Pygofer, dorsal view; F. Pygofer, ventral view; G. Pygofer, lateral view; H. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; I. Connective and style, ventral view; J. Aedeagus, dorsal view. K, L Paratype: K. Pygofer, lateral view; L. Pygofer, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1953,2015]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,153,359]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,237,1953,1979]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Length</emphasis>
(including forewing): 
<specimenCount box="[491,512,1953,1979]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
<quantity box="[519,711,1953,1979]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.14" metricValueMax="1.172" metricValueMin="1.108" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="11.4" valueMax="11.72" valueMin="11.08">11.08–11.72 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,465,1989,2015]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">External morphology.</emphasis>
Body brownish-red to dark brown. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[985,1077,1989,2015]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1900,1925]" captionTargetBox="[163,1414,184,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1430,174,1880]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Balala hainana Tang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. ♂, A–I Holotype: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and thorax, lateral view; D. Habitus, ventral view; E. Pygofer, dorsal view; F. Pygofer, ventral view; G. Pygofer, lateral view; H. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; I. Connective and style, ventral view; J. Aedeagus, dorsal view. K, L Paratype: K. Pygofer, lateral view; L. Pygofer, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
) anterior margin round, length shorter than 1/2 width between eyes. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[1066,1198,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1900,1925]" captionTargetBox="[163,1414,184,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1430,174,1880]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Balala hainana Tang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. ♂, A–I Holotype: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and thorax, lateral view; D. Habitus, ventral view; E. Pygofer, dorsal view; F. Pygofer, ventral view; G. Pygofer, lateral view; H. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; I. Connective and style, ventral view; J. Aedeagus, dorsal view. K, L Paratype: K. Pygofer, lateral view; L. Pygofer, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635596/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">Figs. 8A, C</figureCitation>
) truncated well short of clavus, exposed part of mesonotum about 1/6–1/4 scutellum length, scutellum with centre compressed into keel vertically and truncate subapically in lateral view, median longitudinal ridge moderately weak and extended through entire scutellum or not. Forewing with one indistinct transparent band present between apical cells and appendix. Abdomen with pair of continuous yellow patches on 3rd to 5th tergites submedially. Hind femur with 4–5 macrosetae at apex, tibia with ca. 9–10, 12 setae in rows AD, PD, respectively.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635592" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3635592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635592/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" startId="11.[151,250,1718,1743]" targetBox="[179,1400,384,1687]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1718,1815]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1718,1743]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">FIGURE 6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Tang &amp; Zhang" authorityName="Tang &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2020" box="[280,576,1718,1743]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujiana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[280,425,1718,1742]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">Balala fujiana</emphasis>
Tang &amp; Zhang
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[581,661,1719,1743]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[581,661,1719,1743]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
♂, A–E Holotype: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D. Face; E. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum, dorsal view. F, G. Paratypes: Habitus, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1860,2031]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,376,1860,1887]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[485,560,1861,1887]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1900,1925]" captionTargetBox="[163,1414,184,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1430,174,1880]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Balala hainana Tang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. ♂, A–I Holotype: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and thorax, lateral view; D. Habitus, ventral view; E. Pygofer, dorsal view; F. Pygofer, ventral view; G. Pygofer, lateral view; H. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; I. Connective and style, ventral view; J. Aedeagus, dorsal view. K, L Paratype: K. Pygofer, lateral view; L. Pygofer, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635596/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">Figs. 8</figureCitation>
E–G, L, K) with dorsal inner margin nearly straight, subapex of ventral margin round or a little angulate, many small short setae arranged along ventral margin; ventral appendage approaching or even reaching apex of pygofer, gradually curved dorsad. Subgenital plate about as long as 1/2 pygofer side. Apical margin of connective (
<figureCitation box="[405,481,1969,1995]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1900,1925]" captionTargetBox="[163,1414,184,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1430,174,1880]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Balala hainana Tang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. ♂, A–I Holotype: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and thorax, lateral view; D. Habitus, ventral view; E. Pygofer, dorsal view; F. Pygofer, ventral view; G. Pygofer, lateral view; H. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; I. Connective and style, ventral view; J. Aedeagus, dorsal view. K, L Paratype: K. Pygofer, lateral view; L. Pygofer, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635596/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">Figs. 8</figureCitation>
H–J) nearly straight; style about 1.5x longer than connective; aedeagus shaft tubular, apical half of dorsal surface rugulose, preatrium slightly longer than shaft, gonopore at shaft apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
